The paper discusses the integration of marketing channels into a social network, which falls under the category of social influence (cs.SI). The paper also proposes a framework for allocating budget among these channels, which involves optimization and decision-making, falling under the categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and decision making (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of viral marketing and social media, which falls under the category of social networks (cs.SOC). Finally, the paper discusses marketing strategies, which falls under the category of marketing (cs.MKTG).
